Those aged 25 to 34 have the least amount of time to themselves -LRB- 13 hours per week -RRB- , eight hours less than the national average of 21 hours .

Given more me time a week , people would indulge in their favorite hobbies and interests including reading -LRB- 44 per cent -RRB- , listen to more music -LRB- 31 per cent -RRB- , watch quality TV -LRB- 30 per cent -RRB- , go for more walks or simply just catch up on sleep -LRB- both 29 per cent -RRB- .

